		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>Effective methods of capacity control via uniform convergence bounds for function expansions have been largely limited to Support Vector machines , where good bounds are obtainable by the entropy number approach. We extend these methods to systems with expansions in terms of arbitrary (parametrized) basis functions and a wide range of regulariza-tion methods covering the whole range of general linear additive models. This is achieved by a data dependent analysis of the eigenvalues of the corresponding design matrix.</p>
			</abstract>
